{"type":"message","id":"ea5e4d51","parentId":"64d90713","timestamp":"2026-05-03T21:04:06.714Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session shows last interaction at 1777781388536 (ms timestamp). Let me check the jsonl file mtime vs the state file to see if there's a mismatch.\n\nThe jsonl file path is: /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/agents/finn/sessions/7806b05e-50ec-44ff-86e0-ceaf9c1aed4b.jsonl\n\nThe state file is: ~/.openclaw/agents/finn/sessions/7806b05e-50ec-44ff-86e0-ceaf9c1aed4b\n\nWait, no. The state file is at `~/.openclaw/agents/finn/sessions/7806b05e-50ec-44ff-86e0-ceaf9c1aed4b` but the script looks for the jsonl file at `sessions_dir / f\"{session_id}.jsonl\"`.\n\nWait, looking at the script again - the state key is `finn_jsonl_mtime`. The script checks `state.get(state_key) == mtime`. If the file hasn't been modified since the last run, it says \"No new messages\". \n\nLet me check what mtime is stored in the state file and what the actual mtime of the jsonl is.\n","thinkingSignature":"386a564908271b323a4748770a83f89e9391f3ea7db55d911b14ab461edd95c0"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me check the state file and compare mtimes:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tuvept15uukq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/finn/sessions/.heartbeat_logger_state.json 2>/dev/null || echo \"no state file\"; ls -la ~/.openclaw/agents/finn/sessions/7806b05e-50ec-44ff-86e0-ceaf9c1aed4b.jsonl"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":14154,"output":372,"cacheRead":18368,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32894,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777842237248,"responseId":"0646eb3d27a0356e9102854a76820db9"}}
