{"type":"message","id":"92531c32","parentId":"3f45d5ba","timestamp":"2026-05-03T21:04:13.454Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - the state file doesn't exist but the script says \"No new messages for finn\". The jsonl file was last modified at May 3 00:10 (0:10 AM), which is about 21 hours ago. There's no state file yet, so the mtime wasn't saved.\n\nThe script loads state from `~/.openclaw/agents/finn/sessions/.heartbeat_logger_state.json` (a file inside the sessions dir), but the actual STATE_FILE in the script is:\n```python\nSTATE_FILE = WIKI_ROOT / \".heartbeat_logger_state.json\"\n```\nwhich is `~/agent-mission-control/memory-wiki/.heartbeat_logger_state.json`\n\n\nLet me check if that file exists and what it contains.\n","thinkingSignature":"b22bed7097a398fc323871f1264d1a024f792cee77f1e3d3c74854e731b710df"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fn1dmbh1kll1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/agent-mission-control/memory-wiki/.heartbeat_logger_state.json 2>/dev/null || echo \"no state file\"; stat -f \"%Sm\" ~/.openclaw/agents/finn/sessions/7806b05e-50ec-44ff-86e0-ceaf9c1aed4b.jsonl"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":184,"output":245,"cacheRead":32512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32941,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777842246813,"responseId":"0646eb46eb6faba404ad9ed935c07aa1"}}
